AAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":null,"claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":null,"comments":[],"created_at":1784581489018061001,"creation_channel":"import","deps":[],"description":"## Finding\n\nThe verification pipeline intentionally tolerates and repairs provider/model output variations, but a structurally divergent response can currently normalize to an empty result that is treated like a valid review outcome.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/verify_models.py:143-161` shows tolerant Pydantic parsing can ignore unexpected keys and produce an empty model.\n- `src/rebar/llm/verify_models.py:26-32` registers the live verification model without enabling strict-only parsing.\n- `docs/adr/0006-llm-stage-seam-contracts.md:14-35` records the historical risk of malformed output yielding misleadingly green reviews.\n- `docs/adr/0006-llm-stage-seam-contracts.md:94-154` intentionally adopts tolerant expand-contract parsing, telemetry, and staged tightening.\n\n## Remediation\n\nPreserve flexible parsing, normalization, bounded retries, and provider-independent self-healing. A recovered, semantically non-empty response remains valid. A semantically empty response is never a valid verification result; after recovery attempts it must become an explicit indeterminate or contract-failure outcome. Telemetry must distinguish clean parses, recovered parses, empty outcomes, and unrecoverable responses.\n\nCascade flag: behavior applies across providers and model versions; avoid schema rigidity that converts recoverable format variation into review fragility.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Clean preferred-schema responses continue to validate normally.\n- [ ] Recoverable non-empty responses from supported provider/model variations are normalized and accepted.\n- [ ] Semantically empty verification results can never produce a valid pass or valid empty review.\n- [ ] Empty-after-recovery and unrecoverable responses produce a distinct explicit indeterminate or contract-failure outcome.\n- [ ] Bounded retry/self-healing behavior remains provider-independent and deterministic at the orchestration boundary.\n- [ ] Telemetry separately counts clean parses, recovered parses, semantically empty outcomes, and unrecoverable responses.\n- [ ] Tests cover representative alternate wrappers/field shapes, successful recovery, empty normalization, retry exhaustion, and provider-version variation.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/llm/verify_models.py","reason":"Flexible response parsing and semantic-empty detection"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm","reason":"Retry, outcome, and telemetry integration"},{"path":"docs/adr/0006-llm-stage-seam-contracts.md","reason":"Contract and rollout decision record"},{"path":"tests","reason":"Provider-shape recovery and empty-outcome coverage"}],"keyring":[],"managed_refs":[["parent","6eca-183e-1cd2-4fb9"]],"parent_id":"6eca-183e-1cd2-4fb9","parent_status_uuid":"","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":1,"reverts":[],"source_author":"ChatGPT","source_created_at":1784525665039945864,"source_env":"0af3c941-9543-4bc4-a360-bc56759da47a","source_id":"9637-f459-648f-4882","status":"open","tags":["janitor","llm","verification","resilience"],"ticket_id":"1aa8-cdde-4ff6-40d0","ticket_type":"story","title":"Reject empty verifier outcomes while preserving resilient parsing","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["1123376d-dcb5-4ac0-8b8e-8e204bdbb911","8f49f773-3696-4985-9190-e398554ecddb","224c4a02-6d82-48b0-bc41-68f1600ab633"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784581496030150002,"uuid":"5eceb124-46af-41e2-8fde-070f3f9bd655"}